children.name: Object

children.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all [Object]s is to return true if and
only if [:this:] and [other] are the same object.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override
the [hashCode] method as well to maintain consistency.

children.name: toString
children.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

children.name: noSuchMethod
children.comment:
[noSuchMethod] is invoked when users invoke a non-existant method
on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the
invocation are passed to [noSuchMethod] in an [InvocationMirror].
If [noSuchMethod] returns a value, that value becomes the result of
the original invocation.

The default behavior of [noSuchMethod] is to throw a
[noSuchMethodError].

children.name: hashCode
children.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the
same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality
operator [:==:]. Other than that there are no guarantees about
the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and
there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides [hashCode] it should override the
equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

children.name: runtimeType
children.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

children.name: Object
children.comment:
Creates a new [Object] instance.

[Object] instances have no meaningful state, and are only useful
through their identity. An [Object] instance is equal to itself
only.
Everything in Dart is an [Object].

children.name: setFillColorRgb
children.comment:
Sets the color used inside shapes.
[r], [g], [b] are 0-255, [a] is 0-1.

children.name: setFillColorHsl
children.comment:
Sets the color used inside shapes.
[h] is in degrees, 0-360.
[s], [l] are in percent, 0-100.
[a] is 0-1.

children.name: setStrokeColorRgb
children.comment:
Sets the color used for stroking shapes.
[r], [g], [b] are 0-255, [a] is 0-1.

children.name: setStrokeColorHsl
children.comment:
Sets the color used for stroking shapes.
[h] is in degrees, 0-360.
[s], [l] are in percent, 0-100.
[a] is 0-1.

CanvasRenderingContext
canvas
children.comment: Reference to the canvas element to which this context belongs.

A rendering context for a canvas element.

This context is extended by [CanvasRenderingContext2D] and
[WebGLRenderingContext].

children.name: cq
children.comment:
Create a [CqWrapper] object using a [selector]. The [selector] can be a
a String that should be used to query the DOM or an existing [CanvasElement]
or [ImageElement] that should be wrapped.

To create a new [CqWrapper] object with a specific size the [selector]
argument will take an [int] argoument for the width.

If no argument is given, the size of the window will be used for the new
[CanvasElement].

children.name: CqWrapper
noSuchMethod
children.comment: Delegates to the wrapped [CanvasRenderingContext2D].

children.name: appendTo
children.comment: Appends the canvas to [element].

children.name: replaceWith
children.comment:
Replaces the wrapped [CanvasElement] and [CanvasRenderingContext2D] in this
[CqWrapper] object and in the DOM.

children.name: blendOn
children.comment: Blends the canvas of this object onto [what] using [mode] and [mix].

children.name: blend
children.comment:
Blends the object [what] ([CqWrapper], [CanvasElement], [ImageElement] or
color) onto this canvas using [mode] and [mix].

children.name: blendColor
children.comment: Blends the color [what] onto this canvas using [mode] and [mix].

children.name: blendSpecial
children.comment:
Blends the object [what] ([CqWrapper], [CanvasElement], [ImageElement] or
color) onto this canvas using [mode] and [mix].

children.name: blendSpecialColor
children.comment: Blends the color [what] onto this canvas using [mode] and [mix].

children.name: strokeAndFill
children.comment:
Calls [stroke()] if [strokeStyle] is set.
Calls [fill()] if [fillStyle] is set.
The values of strokeStyle and fillStyle on the wrapped
[CanvasRenderingContext2D] will only be changed for the call
to this function and will be reset afterwards.

children.name: circle
children.comment: Draws a circls at [x], [y] with [radius].

children.name: crop
children.comment: Crops the canvas.

children.name: resize
children.comment:
Resizes the canvas. If only [width] or [height] is passed, the image will
be resized proportionally.

children.name: trim
children.comment:
Trims the canvas using [color] as the transparent color. If no [color] is
provided transparent pixels will be used to determine the size of the
trimmed canvas.

Returns a [Rect] with the trim boundaries or null if nothing was trimmed.

children.name: resizePixel
children.comment: Resizes the canvas by using [pixelSize] to resize each pixel (no bluring).

children.name: matchPalette
children.comment: Reduces the colors of the image to the colors in the [palette].

children.name: getPalette
children.comment: Returns a [List<String>] of the colors used in the canvas.

children.name: pixelize
children.comment: Pixelizes the canvas.

children.name: colorToMask
children.comment:
Returns a mask containing [true] for every pixel that does not have color [hexColor].
The mask will contain [true] for every other pixel if [inverted] is set to [true].

children.name: grayscaleToMask
children.comment:
Returns a grayscale maks of the canvas. Each value in the returned list
will be the average of the RGB-values.

children.name: grayscaleToAlpha
children.comment:
Converts grayscale of an image to its transparency.
Light pixels become opaque. Dark pixels become transparent.

children.name: applyMask
children.comment:
Applies a mask.
For a mask of [bool] every [true] value will turn a pixel transparent.
For a grayscalemask of [int] values, black will turn a pixel transparent.

children.name: fillMask
children.comment:
Fills the canvas using [hexColor] for [true] and
[hexColorGradient] for [false] bits in the [mask]. If the mask is a
grayscale, a gradient between both colors will be created.

children.name: clear
children.comment: Clears the canvas with [color]. Calls [clearRect()] if no color is passed.

children.name: copy
children.comment: Creates a new [CanvasElement] with the same size and content as this canvas.

children.name: setHslAsList
children.comment: Sets the hue, saturation and lightness of the image.

children.name: setHsl
children.comment: Sets the [hue], [saturation] and [lightness] of the image.

children.name: shiftHslAsList
children.comment: Shifts the hue, saturation and lightness of the image by the passes amount.

children.name: shiftHsl
children.comment: Shifts the [hue], [saturation] and [lightness] of the image by the passes amount.

children.name: replaceHue
children.comment: Replaces the hue of 0<=[src]<=1 with 0<=[dst]<=1.

children.name: invert
children.comment: Inverts the colors of the image.

children.name: roundRect
children.comment: Creates a rect with rounded corners.

children.name: gradientText
children.comment:
Creates a [text] with [gradient] colors. If a [maxWidth] is set the [text]
will wrap around at [maxWidth].
The [gradient] is a list of color stops and colors.
E.g.
    [0, '#000000', 0.5, '#FF0000', 1, '#0000FF']

children.name: wrappedText
children.comment:
Writes [text] at [x], [y] and wraps at [maxWidth].

The [nlCallback] will be called before a line is written.

children.name: textBoundaries
children.comment:
Returns a [Rect] with the size of a given [text]. If [maxWidth]
is given, the [text] will be wrapped.

children.name: getLines
children.comment: Splits the [text] at [maxWidth] and returns a list of lines.

children.name: paperBag
children.comment: Creates a paper bag shaped path.

children.name: borderImage
children.comment:
Creates an expandable area with borders from [image].
[x], [y], [width], [height] are the values for the border.
[top], [right], [bottom], [left] are the boundaries of the border in the
[image].

children.name: convolve
children.comment:
Convolve an image using [matrix].
See <www.html5rocks.com/en/tutorials/canvas/imagefilters/>.

children.name: blur
children.comment: Blurs an image.

children.name: gaussianBlur
children.comment: Applies a gaussian blur to an image.

children.name: sharpen
children.comment: Sharpens the image.

children.name: threshold
children.comment: Pixels with a grayscale value beyond [threshold] will become transparent.

children.name: sepia
children.comment: Sepia filter.

children.name: canvas
children.comment: The wrapped [CanvasElement].

children.name: context2d
children.comment: The wrapped [CanvasRenderingContext2D].

children.name: framework
children.comment: The [CqFramework] to access several Event-[Stream]s.

children.name: CqWrapper
children.comment: Wrap an existing [CanvasElement].

children.name: CqWrapper.forWindow
children.comment: Creates and wrap a [CanvasElement] covering the whole window. Resizing included.

children.name: CqWrapper.query
children.comment: Queries a {CanvasElement] from the DOM and wraps it.

children.name: CqWrapper.forSize
children.comment: Creates and wraps a [CanvasElement] with the given [width] and [height].

children.name: CqWrapper.forImage
children.comment: Creates and wraps a [CanvasElement] using the given image.

Wrapper around [CanvasElement] and [CanvasRenderingContext2D] offering
additional functionality.

children.name: blend
children.comment: Blends [below] with [above] using [blendingFunction].

children.name: blendSpecial
children.comment: Blends [below] with [above] using [blendingFunction].

children.name: createCanvas
children.comment: Draws an [img] on a [CanvasElement] and returns the canvas.

children.name: createImageData
children.comment: Creates an [ImageData] object for the size of [width] and [height].

children.name: mousePosition
children.comment:
Calculates the position of the mouse.

See <https://gist.github.com/3781251>

children.name: CqStepEvent
children.comment:
Event that is produced by some of the Streams in [CqFramework] with timing
data.

children.name: CqMouseEvent
children.comment:
Event that is produced by some of the Streams in [CqFramework] with basic
information about a mouse event.

children.name: CqFramework
onStep
children.comment:
Fires a [CqStepEvent] every time [interval] has passed.

Can be used for game logic. Will fire new events even if the browser
tab is inactive.

children.name: onSwipe
children.comment: Returns a [Stream] of swipe direction.

children.name: onRender
children.comment:
Fires a [CqStepEvent] when `window.animationFrame`'s future executes.

Can be used for rendering. Will not fire events while the browser tab is
inactive.

children.name: onMouseMove
children.comment:
Fires a [CqMouseEvent] when an `onMouseMove` or an `onTouchMove` event
is fired.

children.name: onMouseDown
children.comment:
Fires a [CqMouseEvent] when an `onMouseDown` or an `onTouchSouch` event
is fired.

children.name: onMouseUp
children.comment:
Fires a [CqMouseEvent] when an `onMouseUp` or an `onTouchEnd` event
is fired.

children.name: onKeyDown
children.comment: Returns a stream of [KeyCode].

children.name: onKeyUp
children.comment: Returns a stream of [KeyCode].

children.name: onResize
children.comment: Returns a Stream of [Rect] for the new size of the window.

children.name: onDropImage
children.comment: Returns a [Stream} of dropped [ImageElement].
A simple framework for easy access to events created by the canvas.
